},{"section":20,"text":"The tubular vision is from the progressive loss of peripheral visual field, leading to tunnel vision.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039257,0.075489,0.080333,0.085689,0.091632,0.096249,0.098529,0.096717,0.093186,0.088146,0.0817,0.073073],"unified_progress":[0.062558,0.068489,0.076082,0.081919,0.08847,0.09551,0.093794,0.095825,0.094356,0.090146,0.082899,0.069952]},{"section":21,"text":"The fundus findings of arteriole attenuation might be a red herring, or maybe part of the disease progression.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035871,0.0729,0.084083,0.090875,0.093681,0.095982,0.097051,0.09417,0.095473,0.088018,0.0803,0.071594],"unified_progress":[0.044356,0.069176,0.083871,0.092755,0.098191,0.098132,0.097569,0.094433,0.094703,0.086917,0.076269,0.063627]},{"section":22,"text":"The waxy pallor of the optic disc could be due to secondary atrophy from long-standing retinal disease, or maybe another process.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035491,0.072971,0.083824,0.091905,0.094967,0.097911,0.098273,0.094002,0.096887,0.085931,0.077723,0.070115],"unified_progress":[0.043716,0.067381,0.083932,0.094759,0.10044,0.10065,0.099167,0.095014,0.094997,0.083612,0.073639,0.062698]},{"section":23,"text":"But given the pigment changes and the visual symptoms, RP is the most likely.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029839,0.065441,0.082754,0.089011,0.089828,0.087925,0.090457,0.089445,0.090275,0.095242,0.089037,0.10075],"unified_progress":[0.030905,0.05633,0.06851,0.079958,0.084181,0.086724,0.090856,0.094478,0.097068,0.10197,0.10357,0.10544]},{"section":24,"text":"Ring scotomas in RP can occur as the disease progresses, with the outer vision lost first, creating a ring-shaped scotoma.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037099,0.070872,0.078667,0.086894,0.092842,0.096267,0.098275,0.095614,0.093858,0.089724,0.082848,0.07704],"unified_progress":[0.049808,0.06148,0.074361,0.085365,0.091145,0.097525,0.096644,0.09767,0.096908,0.092356,0.083855,0.072882]},{"section":25,"text":"Alternatively, maybe the ring scotoma is from another cause, but the combination of bone spicules, night blindness, and the visual field changes all point to RP.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031467,0.063335,0.074684,0.082498,0.08856,0.092263,0.096211,0.09638,0.098008,0.096627,0.093448,0.086518],"unified_progress":[0.039221,0.058707,0.07168,0.081442,0.08889,0.094524,0.096234,0.098268,0.099758,0.098961,0.09257,0.079744]},{"section":26,"text":"The normal IOP rules out glaucoma as the primary issue.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028376,0.062583,0.077036,0.084594,0.089101,0.092179,0.096583,0.096936,0.097486,0.095884,0.091929,0.087312],"unified_progress":[0.035212,0.062754,0.074505,0.082454,0.088974,0.091696,0.094577,0.096558,0.097326,0.097872,0.093831,0.084241]},{"section":27,"text":"So the diagnosis is retinitis pigmentosa.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021287,0.042917,0.05241,0.06035,0.068809,0.076592,0.084228,0.089725,0.098213,0.10241,0.11734,0.18571],"unified_progress":[0.021131,0.031855,0.040111,0.049719,0.05525,0.067548,0.071764,0.085753,0.098081,0.10912,0.1528,0.21687]}]}}